    • Class net.hudup.core.alg.Recommender extends AbstractAlg implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • filterList

          FilterList filterList
          The filter list contains of filters. Filter specifies tasks which be performed before any actual recommendation tasks. Concretely, two methods Recommender.estimate(RecommendParam, Set) and Recommender.recommend(RecommendParam, int) require filtering tasks specified by filters of this list. Suppose every item has types 1, 2, 3, an example of filtering task is to select only type-1 items for recommendation task, which means that the list of recommended items produced by the method Recommender.recommend(RecommendParam, int) later contains only type-1 items.

Account is the information of a user who has access to the server with her/his privileges. Account is modeled and stored in framework database as profile.

        • attribute

          java.lang.String attribute
          Attribute name. Note, attribute represented by Attribute class indicates the data type, which is also a wrapper of data type. Each attribute has always a name.

        • condition

          Condition is the special profile which is used in condition clause where in SQL statement for processing database, for example.

          Item identifier (item ID) is stored in outside database different from the Hudup database.

          External record represented by ExternalRecord class is a record (a row in table) which is stored in other database (different from the framework database). It is opposite to internal record represented by InternalRecord class which is a record stored in the framework database.

        • external_userid

          java.io.Serializable external_userid
          User identifier (user ID) is stored in outside database different from the Hudup database.

        • file_type

          int file_type
          File type such as Hudup file type (*.hdp), text file type (*.txt), CSV file type (*.csv), etc.

        • file_path

          java.lang.String file_path
          File path such as C:/Hudup/datasets/movielens/rating001.test

        • internal_record

          InternalRecord internal_record
          Internal record represented by InternalRecord class is a record (a row in table) stored in the framework database.

        • itemid

          int itemid
          Item identifier (item ID).

        • host

          java.lang.String host
          The host where Hudup server is deployed, for examle, "localhost".

        • max_recommend

          int max_recommend
          Recommendation service produces a list of recommended item. This variable specifies the maximum number of recommended items.

        • nominal

          Nominal nominal
          Nominal data indicates discrete and non-number data such as weekdays {Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday}. Nominal data is called nominal, in brief, represented by Nominal class.

        • nominal_ref_unit

          java.lang.String nominal_ref_unit
          The unit name of nominal (s). Note, nominal data indicates discrete and non-number data such as weekdays {Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday}. Nominal data is called nominal, in brief, represented by Nominal class. Unit represents a CSV file, database table, Excel sheet, etc. Unit is used to store object such as user profile, item profile, rating matrix, etc.

        • port

          int port
          The port where Hudup server serves incoming requests. As ususal, the port of recommendation server is 10151.

        • profile

          Profile profile
          Specified profile. Note, Profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses a attribute list to specify its data types. Every object can be modeled as profile to be stored in archive (file).

        • queryids

          java.util.Set<E> queryids
          Specified set of identifiers (IDs). Such IDs can be user IDs or item IDs.

        • rating_vector

          RatingVector rating_vector
          Note, rating vector represented RatingVector contains ratings. If rating vector is user rating vector, it contains all ratings of the same user on many items. If rating vector is item rating vector, it contains all ratings of many users on the same item.

        • rating

          Rating rating
          This is a rating that a user gives on an item, represented by Rating class.

        • recommend_param

          RecommendParam recommend_param
          Specified recommendation parameter represented by RecommendParam. Recommendation parameter contains important information as follows:
          • Initial rating vector which can be user rating vector or item rating vector.
          • A profile which can be user profile containing user information (ID, name, etc.) or item profile containing item information (ID, name, price, etc.).
          • A context list relevant to how and where user (s) rates (rate) on item (s).
          • Additional information must be serializable.

        • reg_name

          java.lang.String reg_name
          Registered name of recommendlet. Recommendlet represented by Recommendlet class is service or a small graphic user interface (GUI) that allows users to see and interact with a list of recommended items. Recommendlet is now deprecated.

        • session_attribute_name

          java.lang.String session_attribute_name
          Specified name of the current session in server. Hudup server (recommendation server) serves all incoming request in a time interval (a period in mili-seconds). Such time interval is called session. Each session has a number of attributes. Each attribute is a pair of key and value. Key is also called name. When it is time-out which means that the server has received no request after the time interval then, the session is destroyed, which causes that all attributes are destroyed.

        • sql

          java.lang.String sql
          Specified SQL statement. Note, SQL which is abbreviation of Structured Query Language is a formal language for accessing relation database.

        • unit

          java.lang.String unit
          Specified unit name. Unit represents a CSV file, database table, Excel sheet, etc. Unit is used to store object such as user profile, item profile, rating matrix, etc.

        • userid

          int userid
          User identifier (user ID).

        • fProfile

          Fetcher<E> fProfile
          Fetcher to retrieves many profiles. Fetcher is the interface for iterating each element of an associated collection. Note, profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses a attribute list to specify its data types. Every object can be modeled as profile to be stored in archive (file).

          Fetcher<E> fRating
          Fetcher to retrieves many rating vectors. Fetcher is the interface for iterating each element of an associated collection. Note, rating vector represented RatingVector contains ratings. If rating vector is user rating vector, it contains all ratings of the same user on many items. If rating vector is item rating vector, it contains all ratings of many users on the same item.

        • nominalList

Nominal data indicates discrete and non-number data such as weekdays {Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday}. Nominal data is called nominal, in brief, represented by Nominal class.

        • profile

          Profile profile
          Result as profile. Note, profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses a attribute list to specify its data types. Every object can be modeled as profile to be stored in archive (file).

        • recommendlet

          Recommendlet recommendlet
          Deprecated. 
          Result as recommendlet. Recommendlet represented by Recommendlet class is a service or a small graphic user interface (GUI) that allows users to see and interact with a list of recommended items. Recommendlet is now deprecated.

        • snapshot

          Snapshot snapshot
          Result as snapshot. Snapshot is an image of dataset owned by Hudup server at current time point, stored in memory. Snapshot is represented by Snapshot class.

        • stringResult

          java.lang.String stringResult

        • vRating

          RatingVector vRating
          Result as rating vector. Note, rating vector represented RatingVector contains ratings. If rating vector is user rating vector, it contains all ratings of the same user on many items. If rating vector is item rating vector, it contains all ratings of many users on the same item.

        • externalRecord

          ExternalRecord externalRecord
          Result as external record. Note, external record represented by ExternalRecord class is a record (a row in table) which is stored in other database (different from the framework database). It is opposite to internal record represented by InternalRecord class which is a record stored in the framework database.

    • Class net.hudup.core.data.Attribute extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          Name of attribute.

        • type

          Attribute.Type type
          Internal data type of this attribute. Default value of this type is Attribute.Type.object (anything).

        • index

          int index
          The index of this attribute. This index is only meaningful if this attribute is a member of attribute list. Note that attribute list is represented by AttributeList. For example, if this attribute is the first element in attribute list, its index is 0. When the index is -1, this attribute is not attached with any attribute list. Default value of this index is -1.

        • isKey

          boolean isKey
          If this value is true, this attribute is key attribute used to distinguish two records (two profiles). Exactly, in a profile, a key attribute or a set of some key attributes are used to distinguish two profiles. If there is only one key attribute, we state that the profile has single key. A integer single key is also called identification (ID). If there are a set of key attributes, we state that the profile has complex key. Single key and complex key are represented by the Keys class. Default value of this variable is false.

        • autoInc

          boolean autoInc
          If this value is true, this attribute is auto-increment attribute. For example, suppose a record (profile) whose first value is an integer and has auto-increment attribute; when a new record (profile) is inserted, the value of such record is increased automatically. Default value of this variable is false. Note that the auto-increment is only effective if this attribute has integer type; otherwise, the auto-increment is ignored.

        • nominalList

          NominalList nominalList
          In case that type of this attribute indicates nominal type called nominal in brief, this variable is the list of nominal (s). Nominal indicates discrete and non-number data such as weekdays (Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday). Nominal is represented by Nominal and nominal list is represented by NominalList. This variable is the empty nominal list.

    • Class net.hudup.core.data.ParamSql extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • sql

          java.lang.String sql
          This variable is a string specifying parametric SQL statement in text. The parametric SQL statement has many question masks. Each question mark indicates a parameter where real value is filled in when the parametric SQL statement is completed for accessing database. Indices of these question marks are specified by variable ParamSql.indexes.

        • indexes

          java.util.List<E> indexes
          This variable called parametric indexer specifies indices of parameters inside the parametric SQL statement referred by the variable ParamSql.sql. The parametric SQL statement has many question masks. Each question mark indicates a parameter where real value is filled in when the parametric SQL statement is completed for accessing database. For ease of understanding, indices of these question marks are specified by this variable. This variable is a list and so if it is empty, the SQL statement has no parameter.

    • Class net.hudup.core.data.RatingVector extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • id

          int id
          If this class is user rating vector which contains all ratings of the same user on many items then, this internal variable is user identification (user ID). If this class is item rating vector which contains all ratings of many users on the same item then, this internal variable is item identification (item ID). As a convention, this variable is known as ID of rating vector.

        • ratedMap

          java.util.Map<K,V> ratedMap
          This map contains all ratings of this rating vector. Each entry of this map has a key and a value. Value is rating represented by Rating class. If this class is user rating vector which contains all ratings of the same user on many items then, key is item identification (item ID). If this class is item rating vector which contains all ratings of many users on the same item then, key is user identification (user ID). As a convention, such key is called field id indicating both user id and item id, which is distinguished with regard that this rating vector is user rating vector or item rating vector. Therefore, every rating is associated with a field ID.
